description.p:
According to a first aspect of the present invention, an optical glass has;
a refractive index (nd) and an Abbe number (νd) which are within an area surrounded by straight lines that are drawn by connecting point A (nd=1.835, νd=46.5), point B (nd=1.90, νd=40.0), point C, (nd=1.90, νd=35.0) and point D (nd=1.835, νd=38.0) in a sequence of A, B, C, D and A as border lines in x-y orthogonal coordinates shown in FIG. 1, in which X-axis is the Abbe number (νd) and Y-axis is the refractive index (nd), the area including the border lines: and the optical glass comprises the following components by mass%:
0.1 to 8% of SiO2;
5 to less than 20% B2O3;
15 to 50% of La2O3;
0.1 to 30% Gd2O3,
0 to 10% of GeO2 and
0 to 8% of Nb2O5, where a total content of Gd2O3 + GeO2 + Nb2O5 is more than 10% to 30%;
0 to 5% of Yb2O3;
0 to 1% of TiO2;
0 to 8% of ZrO2;
more than 10 to 25% of Ta2O5;
0 to 10% of WO3;
0 to 15% of ZnO;
0 to 5% of RO, where RO is one or more kinds of oxides selected from CaO, SrO and BaO;
more than 0.5 to less than 3% of Li2O;
0 to 1% of Sb2O3; and
0.1 to 6% a the total content of fluorides of above-described metal elements as F element with which a part or all of one or more kinds of oxides of above-described metal elements are substituted; wherein the optical glass is free from lead, cadmium, thorium, Y2O3, P2O5, and TeO2, and
the optical glass has a transition temperature (Tg) of 550 to 650°C.

According to the second aspect of the present invention, an optical glass has
a refractive index (nd) and an Abbe number (νd) which are within an area surrounded by straight lines that are drawn by connecting point A (nd=1.835, νd=46.5), point B (nd=1.90, νd=40.0), point C, (nd=1.90, νd=35.0) and point D (nd=1.835, νd=38.0) in a sequence of A, B, C, D and A as border lines in x-y orthogonal coordinates shown in FIG. 1, in which X-axis is the Abbe number (νd) and Y-axis is the refractive index (nd), the area including the border lines: and the optical glass comprises the following components by mass%;
0.1 to 8% of SiO2;
5 to less than 20% B2O3;
15 to 50% of La2O3;
0.1 to 30% Gd2O3,
more than 10 to 25% of Ta2O5; and
more than 0.5 to less than 3% of Li2O;
and
0 to 10% of GeO2 and/or
0 to 8% of Nb2O5, where a total content of Gd2O3 + GeO2 + Nb2O5 is more than 10% to 30%;
and/or
0 to 5% of Yb2O3; and/or
0 to 1% of TiO2; and/or
0 to 8% of ZrO2; and/or
0 to 10% of WO3; and/or
0 to 15% of ZnO; and/or
0 to 5% of RO, where RO is one or more kinds of oxides selected from CaO, SrO and BaO;
and/or
0 to 1% of Sb2O3; and/or
0 to less than 0.5% of Lu2O3; and
0.1 to 6% of the total content of fluorides of above-described metal elements as F element with which a part or all of one or more kinds of oxides of above-described metal elements are substituted; wherein the optical glass is free from lead component, cadmium component, thorium component, Y2O3, P2O5 and TeO2, and
the optical glass has a transition temperature (Tg) of 550 to 650°C.
